cities.name: Los Angeles-Long Beach
cities.weather: Sunny Los Angeles is always bright and warm, with an average temperature of 75 degrees in the afternoon and 57 degrees at night.  The desert climate is very dry, and it rarely rains.

cities.name: San Francisco
cities.weather: San Francisco is temperate, generally cool and foggy in the morning and sunny in the afternoon with a temperature consistently between 55 and 70 degrees Fahrenheit all year round.  Due to the city's microclimates, it can be sunny and warm in one neighborhood and foggy and cold a mile away.

cities.name: Boston
cities.weather: Boston has four seasons, ranging from a hot and humid summer to an icy, snowy winter.  New England fall is known for its temperate weather and colorful beauty, as the deciduous trees shed their bright leaves.

cities.name: New York (Manhattan)
cities.weather: New York City has four distinct seasons.  Summers are hot and humid, winters are icy and cold, springs are rainy, and the New England fall is gorgeous when Central Park becomes littered with brightly colored leaves.

cities.name: Philadelphia
cities.weather: Philadelphia is characterized by cold winters and hot, humid summers.  The average temperature falls as low as 32 degrees Fahrenheit in January, but they rise to 76 degrees in July.
